The paper proposes a declarative language for querying Linked Data on the Web, which falls under the area of Semantic Web and Web data management. The paper discusses the syntax and semantics of the language, as well as its expressiveness and computational feasibility. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) and software engineering (SE) aspects, which make these two sub-categories less likely but still possible.
